The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26: Banks will ask for an additional password from their credit card customers from the new year for any transactions conducted over phone following a Reserve Bank direction for making phone banking more secure. According to the RBI guideline, from January all banks will mandatorily decline any telephonic transaction, including the automated interactive voice response services, where the customers do not have a one-time password for such services .                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26: The exchequer will lose Rs 800 crore as the finance ministry has decided not to levy service tax on transport of goods through rail this fiscal. We could have mopped up Rs 800 crore from a 10 per cent service tax on railway freight this fiscal, a finance ministry official said.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26: The Centre will retain its borrowing plan of Rs 4.47 lakh crore this fiscal, despite reducing the size of market mop-up by Rs 10,000 crore earlier this month because of a cash shortage in the system.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26: India has imposed anti-dumping duty of up to 266 per cent on imports of an IT equipment  also used in the telecom sector  to guard the domestic industry from cheap Chinese and Israeli shipments.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 26: Air India today claimed that its revenue and passenger load had improved after its turnaround plan came into operation over a year ago. During April-November this year, Air India recorded a network revenue of Rs 7,250 crore.                                                                                                                          
